# fixpoint_stress_1 — directed fixpoint-family witness (see the .dr header for
# the full round-arithmetic trace). Node set {1..5}; add_edge is @differential.
#
# Batch 1 (SEED — same-round double-claim): chain 1->2->3->4->5. The INSERT
#   fixpoint claims tc13 and tc35 both in round 1; round 2 fires the instance
#   tc(1,5):tc(1,3),tc(3,5) as a same-round double-claim, counted exactly once
#   via the kAddNow frontier bits.
batch
+ add_edge 1 2
+ add_edge 2 3
+ add_edge 3 4
+ add_edge 4 5
end

# Batch 2 (CLOSE CYCLE + add-side stale drops): add the back-edge 5->1. The
#   node set becomes one SCC — every ordered pair tc(i,j) is now derivable,
#   many with multiple cyclic supports. Several tc rows this add would fold are
#   already present, exercising the TryClaimAdd total>0 / !kInI mirror.
batch
+ add_edge 5 1
end

# Batch 3 (REMOVE-THEN-REDERIVE, pure C_r>0): remove the chord 3->4. A large
#   overdelete cone fires, but the surrounding cycle re-supports every pair
#   (C_r>0 after quiescence) so REDERIVE restores them: net tc unchanged.
batch
- add_edge 3 4
end

# Batch 4 (PHANTOM PAIR + mixed both-sides): remove the cycle-closing 5->1 and
#   add the chord 2->5 in ONE batch. Support flips within the batch drive
#   §5.1.1 phantom pairs (- in OVERDELETE, + in INSERT, netting zero); mixed
#   add/remove exercises claim-gate stale drops on both sides.
batch
- add_edge 5 1
+ add_edge 2 5
end
